			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">No clue about the first item, Dalren mentioned. But if you want the deep staff, get a second mage and camp it. 
<br />
You can move invis most of time, you have to kill only one or two see invis mobs on your way to the camp. It is also a great place for the VT shards, saw around 8 pieces in 3 hours.
<br />

<br />
Drop rate depends on luck as usual. The first night we got nothing in 3 hours. I logged at safe spot, soloed the camp on the next day and got my staff within one hour. Also went with my ranger husband there and we got his drop in one hour. You even get exp, because mobs are blue and you will walk away with a few coins and spells. 
<br />

<br />
Easy camp, acceptable drop rates. A nice feature for raiding-mages to replace the shrinking device.
<br />

<br />
Map:
<br />
<a href="http://www.noble-blade.net/forums/uploads/post-2-1057348615.jpg" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.noble-blade.net/forums/uploads/post-2-1057348615.jpg</a><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=598009" target="_blank" class="postlink">Silverrain</a>
<br />
Hoher Erzmagier der <a href="http://drachentaenzer.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Drachentänzer</a>
<br />
Kael Drakkal</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
