			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It wouldnt be a fun thing to solo all your way to the camp as a mage with 12AA. If you come across the see invis mobs, you have to deal with at least 2 mobs at one time. 
<br />

<br />
The break-in at the camp spot can be tricky too if you get 3 mobs. If all of them are warriors you are done. I dont think, you can keep your pet alive without mend and I am not sure, your mana would be enough for chainhealing and an occasional nuke, if you have any time left. Best thing what can happen is a double pull consisting off a warrior and a caster mob. You can fight the warrior mob and ignore the caster, provided that your resists are good enough, which is also a little doubtful with pre-elemental gear. You also cant do those funny caster duels without pet hold, where you nuke the mob and the mob nukes you.
<br />

<br />
Just grab someone else for the move and the break-in. If you lose the roll for the first drop and the other person will leave, you can probably do the camp yourself, when the mobs are splitted once.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=598009" target="_blank" class="postlink">Silverrain</a>
<br />
Hoher Erzmagier der <a href="http://drachentaenzer.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Drachentänzer</a>
<br />
Kael Drakkal</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
